<div id="review_815396045" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/815396045" />
    <a title="Banner" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1166255-banner"><img alt="Banner" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1411437884p2/1166255.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/815396045?book_show_action=true">Jan 07, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Banner" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Banner" href="/user/show/1166255-banner">Banner</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1166255-banner?shelf=sci-fi">sci-fi</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer815396045" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16145271380248063175">I begrudgingly read (listened to audio version) this book, but I&apos;m glad I did. It was a solid &quot;3&quot; read which ain&apos;t that bad. It would have been higher but I took off for originality or the lack thereof. If your familiar with the story of the x-men or have a dozen other franchises (the more recent being Steelhearth by Brandon Sanderson) then you pick right up on the plot. Sure there are some differences, but the broad strokes are the same.<br/><br/>So why did I give it a 3? The suspense really did build, e</span>
  <span id="freeText16145271380248063175" style="display:none">I begrudgingly read (listened to audio version) this book, but I'm glad I did. It was a solid "3" read which ain't that bad. It would have been higher but I took off for originality or the lack thereof. If your familiar with the story of the x-men or have a dozen other franchises (the more recent being Steelhearth by Brandon Sanderson) then you pick right up on the plot. Sure there are some differences, but the broad strokes are the same.<br /><br />So why did I give it a 3? The suspense really did build, even though I saw it coming the plot kept me engaged. The characters were pretty good, even for stereotypes. I appreciated the clear and satisfying ending. There is definitely a foundation for the next book, but I don't feel I "have to" buy it to finish this plot line.<br /><br />I don't always give synopsis in my review, I figure there are plenty better ones already published, so I try to tell you what I'm looking at in deciding to read a work of fiction. Maybe it's the stuff you are looking for also. If so, then this is an enjoyable read, while not great literature it is fun escapism. <br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="16145271380248063175" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


